The paper deals with algorithmic stability and generalization bounds for learning algorithms, which are topics typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. The paper also introduces new analysis tools that may have broader applications, suggesting a possible fit with the data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
